Java Language (OPP), class based

abstract continue for        new      switch
assert   default  goto*      package  synchronized
Boolean  do	   if         private  this    
Break    double   implements protected  throw
byte	    else	   import     public   throws
case	    enum	   instanceof return   transient
Catch    extends  int        try      short   
char	    final	   interface  static   void
Class    finally  long	    strictfp volatile
const*   float	   native     super	   while
(*)unused keywords

true, false, and null count as literals/identifiers

+	Addition	Adds together two values	
-	Subtraction	Subtracts one value from another
*	Multiplication	Multiplies two values	
/	Division	Divides one value by another
%	Modulus	Returns the division remainder		
++	Increment	Increases the value of a variable by 1	
--	Decrement	Decreases the value of a variable by 1

Widening Casting (automatically) - converting a smaller type to a larger type
byte -> short -> char -> int -> long -> float -> double

Narrowing Casting (manually) - converting a larger type to a smaller type
double -> float -> long -> int -> char -> short -> byte

MATH
Math.max(x,y)	Math.min(x,y)	Math.min(x,y)	Math.abs(x)
int randomNum = (int)(Math.random() * 101);  // 0 to 100
Define an If statement
if (condition) { /run code here/ } 
Else
}else{ /run else code here/ }
Loops		break (jumps out of loop)  continue (ends iteration)
While loop -  while (condition) { /run code here/ }
While loop -  for (A start; B end; C increment) { /run code here/ }
Example for (int i = 0; i <= 10; i = i + 2) { /run code here/ }

